<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,649,1179]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">
<bibRefCitation author="Lea, A. M." box="[199,324,829,856]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" pagination="166 - 261" refId="ref26041" refString="Lea, A. M. (1919) Notes on some miscellaneous Coleoptera with descriptions of new species. - Part V. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 43, 166 - 261." type="journal article" year="1919">Lea (1919)</bibRefCitation>
did not define the type series, seeing an unknown number of males (vide Articles 73.1.2, 72.1.1). However, in that paper he unequivocally designated a “Type” with the 
<collectionCode box="[946,1007,865,891]" country="South Africa" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mhew-9czz" name="South African Museum" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">SAM</collectionCode>
registration number I.10792 (vide Article 73.1.1). It is presumably the specimen considered as the 
<typeStatus box="[837,935,901,927]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[976,1136,901,927]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton (1978)</bibRefCitation>
and is the one noted as the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,937,963]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A." box="[289,555,937,964]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" refId="ref25821" refString="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1992) Melolonthinae. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea. Vol. 9. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 174 - 358." type="book" year="1992">Houston &amp; Weir (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[565,725,937,963]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton (1978)</bibRefCitation>
also noted a male 
<typeStatus box="[929,1025,938,964]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">paratype</typeStatus>
with the same data in 
<collectionCode box="[1272,1336,937,963]" country="South Africa" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mhew-9czz" name="South African Museum" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">SAM</collectionCode>
; this was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A." box="[293,561,973,1000]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" refId="ref25821" refString="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1992) Melolonthinae. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea. Vol. 9. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 174 - 358." type="book" year="1992">Houston &amp; Weir (1992)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,649,1179]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">
The placement of the 
<typeStatus box="[441,489,1010,1036]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingRegion box="[614,813,1009,1036]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
is doubtful as the species is otherwise known only from northeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[297,498,1045,1072]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
and the genus is not known from 
<collectingRegion box="[882,1082,1045,1072]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[1096,1245,1045,1071]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton 1978</bibRefCitation>
). I suspect that it should be Beverley, 
<collectingRegion box="[379,578,1081,1108]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[592,683,1081,1107]" degrees="31.10" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" precision="555" value="-31.1">31.10°S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[690,800,1081,1108]" degrees="151.01" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" precision="555" value="151.01">151.01°E</geoCoordinate>
). Edgar Francis du Boulay, who collected the specimens, was the son of Francis du Boulay who originally worked in 
<collectingRegion box="[832,1033,1117,1144]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
but later collected in northern 
<collectingRegion country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="30" pageNumber="481">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Musgrave, A." box="[305,486,1153,1179]" pageId="30" pageNumber="481" refId="ref26486" refString="Musgrave, A. (1932) Bibliography of Australian Entomology 1775 - 1930 with Biographical Notes on Authors and Collectors. Royal Zoological Society of New South Wales, Sydney, 380 pp." type="book" year="1932">Musgrave 1932</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
